{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_22","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' .codex-stage-4-ai-bootstrap-synthesis-2026-04-24.md\"","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_22","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' .codex-stage-4-ai-bootstrap-synthesis-2026-04-24.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Brief — Stage 4 AI: baseline knowledge bootstrap via LLM synthesis (Brief 3 of 3)\n\n**Base:** `main` at the commit where Brief 2 (PR #122) has merged. Verify with `git log origin/main` before branching.\n**Branch:** `feat/stage-4-bootstrap-synthesis`\n**Worktree:** `.codex-worktrees/stage-4-bootstrap-synthesis` (architect will prepare this + run `pnpm install` before you start)\n**Model:** GPT-5.4\n**Effort:** **Extra High**. Genuinely novel: multi-source fetching + chunking + multi-pass LLM synthesis pipeline + admin-facing run-status UI + per-project safety rails. Subtle failure modes under partial source availability.\n\nRelated PRD: https://github.com/nico-kneler-as/as-comms-platform/issues/114\nArchitect plan (local): `.handoff-architect-stage-4-ai-drafting-plan-2026-04-23.md`\n\n## Context\n\nBrief 1 shipped the Draft/Fill button. Brief 2 shipped the `project_knowledge_entries` table + send-time capture + Settings Knowledge tab + one-time ops script to import existing Notion child DBs. This brief closes the loop: when an admin activates a new project, a single \"Generate baseline knowledge\" click spins up the project's canonical/snippet/pattern library from configured source URLs and (for projects with existing Gmail alias history) from the alias's bounded email history.\n\nThe output is candidate rows written to `project_knowledge_entries` with `source_kind='bootstrap_synthesized', approved_for_ai=false`. The admin reviews each candidate in the Knowledge tab shipped by Brief 2 and approves the ones worth keeping.\n\n## Architecture in one paragraph\n\nA new `project_knowledge_source_links` table (migration 0023) stores per-project source URLs by kind (`public_project_page`, `volunteer_homepage`, `training_site`, `gmail_alias_history`, `other`). A per-project Settings panel extends Settings → Projects → [projectId] with a \"Knowledge Sources\" list and a \"Generate baseline knowledge\" button. Clicking the button enqueues a worker task (`bootstrap-project-knowledge`) that, for the given project: (1) fetches each configured URL via a Readability-style HTML extractor; (2) for `gmail_alias_history`, queries bounded outbound+inbound canonical events on the project alias; (3) chunks the extracted content; (4) runs a multi-pass Anthropic synthesis — pass 1 extracts topic candidates, pass 2 classifies each topic into `canonical_reply` / `snippet` / `pattern` and produces the structured row fields; (5) writes each candidate to `project_knowledge_entries` with `source_kind='bootstrap_synthesized', approved_for_ai=false`, plus provenance in `metadataJson` (source excerpt + chunk id). A new per-run status table (`project_knowledge_bootstrap_runs`) tracks progress and cost; the UI polls it every ~5 seconds.\n\n## Pre-work (first task before writing code)\n\n1. Read the companion architect plan (`.handoff-architect-stage-4-ai-drafting-plan-2026-04-23.md`) — Brief 3 section.\n2. Skim `apps/worker/src/jobs/notion-knowledge-sync/` to understand the worker-job pattern.\n3. Skim `apps/web/src/server/ai/` for the Anthropic adapter + prompt-builder pattern (you'll reuse the provider for synthesis).\n4. Verify migration slot `0023` is next free (`ls packages/db/drizzle/*.sql | tail -3`).\n\n## Required environment variables\n\n- No new env vars. Reuses `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `AI_DAILY_CAP_USD`, `NOTION_API_KEY` (optional — only if you want to resolve Notion page URLs).\n- Bootstrap runs are bounded by the same `AI_DAILY_CAP_USD` soft cap — each run accumulates into the daily total and emits a `budget_warn` in the run-status row when over.\n\n## Files to create / change\n\n### 1. Migrations + schema\n\nCreate `packages/db/drizzle/0023_project_knowledge_sources_and_runs.sql`:\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE \"project_knowledge_source_links\" (\n  \"id\" text PRIMARY KEY,\n  \"project_id\" text NOT NULL,\n  \"kind\" text NOT NULL,                   -- 'public_project_page'|'volunteer_homepage'|'training_site'|'gmail_alias_history'|'other'\n  \"label\" text,\n  \"url\" text NOT NULL,\n  \"created_at\" timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  \"updated_at\" timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\nCREATE INDEX \"project_knowledge_source_links_project_idx\"\n  ON \"project_knowledge_source_links\" (\"project_id\");\n\nCREATE TABLE \"project_knowledge_bootstrap_runs\" (\n  \"id\" text PRIMARY KEY,\n  \"project_id\" text NOT NULL,\n  \"status\" text NOT NULL,                  -- 'queued'|'fetching'|'synthesizing'|'writing'|'done'|'error'\n  \"started_at\" timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  \"completed_at\" timestamptz,\n  \"stats_json\" jsonb NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',-- { sourcesFetched, topicsFound, candidatesWritten, costEstimateUsd, budgetWarn }\n  \"error_detail\" text,\n  \"created_at\" timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  \"updated_at\" timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\nCREATE INDEX \"project_knowledge_bootstrap_runs_project_idx\"\n  ON \"project_knowledge_bootstrap_runs\" (\"project_id\", \"started_at\" DESC);\n```\n\nAdd Drizzle table defs in `packages/db/src/schema/tables.ts`. Export. Mirror existing patterns.\n\nAdd record contracts in `packages/contracts/src/stage1-records.ts`:\n- `projectKnowledgeSourceLinkSchema` (kind as z.enum, standard fields)\n- `projectKnowledgeBootstrapRunSchema` (status as z.enum)\n\n### 2. Repositories\n\nAdd to `Stage1RepositoryBundle`:\n- `ProjectKnowledgeSourceLinkRepository`: `list(projectId)`, `upsert(record)`, `deleteById(id)`\n- `ProjectKnowledgeBootstrapRunRepository`: `create(record)`, `findById(id)`, `listByProject(projectId, limit)`, `update(input)`\n\nAdd stubs to all 4 domain test fixtures (`packages/domain/test/{repositories,stage3-last-inbound-alias,timeline,normalization}.test.ts`).\n\nImplement in `packages/db/src/repositories.ts` with Drizzle queries.\n\n### 3. Source fetchers\n\nCreate `apps/worker/src/jobs/bootstrap-project-knowledge/fetchers/`:\n- `html-fetcher.ts`: `fetchAndExtract(url) → { title, markdown, wordCount }`. Use a lightweight extractor — try `@mozilla/readability` + `jsdom` (add as deps). Fallback: if readability can't find main content, grab the full text body.\n- `gmail-alias-history.ts`: `digestAliasHistory({ db, projectAlias, monthsBack }) → { digestMarkdown, threadCount }`. Query `canonical_event_ledger` + `gmail_message_details` for the project's alias, bounded to `monthsBack` (default 24), group by `gmail_thread_id`, pair inbound → outbound within threads, mask names/emails/phones via the same placeholder rules used in Brief 2, return a condensed \"Q:... A:...\" digest (truncated to ~20k chars to fit downstream prompts).\n\n### 4. Synthesis pipeline\n\nCreate `apps/worker/src/jobs/bootstrap-project-knowledge/synthesize.ts`:\n\nTwo LLM passes via the Anthropic provider:\n\n**Pass 1 — topic extraction:**\n- Input: concatenated fetched sources + gmail digest (chunked to fit context).\n- Prompt: \"Extract distinct volunteer-facing topics from the following AS project materials. Output a JSON list of `{ topic: string, evidence: [{sourceExcerpt: string}] }`. Do NOT invent topics not present in the text.\"\n\n**Pass 2 — per-topic classification + row drafting:**\n- Input: one topic at a time + the evidence excerpts.\n- Prompt: \"For this topic, produce a JSON object with: kind ('canonical_reply'|'snippet'|'pattern'), issueType, volunteerStage (or null), questionSummary, replyStrategy (required for canonical_reply + pattern, null otherwise), maskedExample (required for canonical_reply, null otherwise), sourceExcerpt (cite the excerpt used). Follow the tier-1 voice guide when drafting replyStrategy or maskedExample.\"\n\nEach Pass-2 result becomes a candidate row.\n\nCosts: batch prompt caching to avoid re-sending the project context for each pass-2 call. Track per-run token usage via `estimateCostUsd`.\n\n### 5. Worker task + UI wiring\n\nCreate `apps/worker/src/jobs/bootstrap-project-knowledge/run.ts`:\n- Graphile-Worker task `bootstrap-project-knowledge` taking `{ runId, projectId }`.\n- Pulls source links; fetches; synthesizes; writes candidates; updates `project_knowledge_bootstrap_runs.status + stats_json` at each phase transition.\n- Safety rails:\n  - Reject run if no source links (error_detail explains).\n  - Require admin confirmation if `project_knowledge_entries` already has >50 rows for this project (add a `force: boolean` flag to the run record; UI surfaces the confirmation).\n- On Anthropic provider failure, mark run `error` with `error_detail`; do NOT retry automatically (admin decides).\n\nRegister in `apps/worker/src/tasks.ts`.\n\n### 6. Settings UI\n\nEdit `apps/web/app/settings/projects/[projectId]/knowledge/page.tsx` (Brief 2's Knowledge tab):\n- Add a \"Knowledge Sources\" section above the entries table: CRUD for source links.\n- Add a \"Generate baseline knowledge\" button. Disabled when no source links. Shows confirmation dialog when entries > 50 already exist.\n- Add a \"Recent runs\" section showing the last N runs with status + stats + cost.\n- The button enqueues via a new server action `triggerBootstrapAction` that inserts a `project_knowledge_bootstrap_runs` row with `status='queued'` and writes a worker job.\n- Run-status section auto-refreshes (simple 5s poll of a new server action or just reload the page; keep it simple).\n\n### 7. Documentation\n\n- `docs/03-reference/reference-env.md` — no new env vars; mention the bootstrap job + `@mozilla/readability` dep.\n- Do NOT edit canon (`docs/01-core/*`, `docs/02-bundles/*`).\n\n## Tests\n\n- `apps/worker/test/bootstrap-synthesis/html-fetcher.test.ts` — fixtures for typical HTML pages + garbage HTML + empty body.\n- `apps/worker/test/bootstrap-synthesis/gmail-alias-history.test.ts` — masking + digest shape with fake events.\n- `apps/worker/test/bootstrap-synthesis/synthesize.test.ts` — Pass 1 + Pass 2 snapshot tests with mocked Anthropic client; cover empty-topic and malformed-JSON responses.\n- `apps/worker/test/bootstrap-synthesis/run.test.ts` — full pipeline happy path + each safety rail.\n- `apps/web/tests/unit/settings-knowledge-sources.test.tsx` — RTL: source link CRUD, bootstrap button gate, confirmation dialog.\n\nCI gate: `pnpm typecheck && pnpm lint && pnpm test:unit` before PR. If macOS rollup gotcha trips locally, note it in the PR description.\n\n## Acceptance / definition of done\n\n- CI green.\n- Migration 0023 applies cleanly.\n- Settings → Knowledge tab shows the new Sources section + Generate button.\n- With source links configured on a test project, clicking Generate creates a `project_knowledge_bootstrap_runs` row and the worker writes candidate entries to `project_knowledge_entries` with `source_kind='bootstrap_synthesized', approved_for_ai=false`.\n- Run-status section shows the run progressing from queued → fetching → synthesizing → writing → done.\n- Gmail-alias-history fetcher produces a masked digest that preserves topic signal (spot-check: no names, emails, phone numbers in output).\n- Safety rails: running on a project with no source links errors gracefully; running on a project with >50 existing entries requires explicit confirmation.\n- No regression in Brief 1 draft or Brief 2 capture flows.\n\n## What NOT to do\n\n- Do NOT add new LLM vendors. Use only Anthropic.\n- Do NOT auto-approve bootstrap-generated candidates. Admin review in the Knowledge tab is mandatory.\n- Do NOT make the bootstrap run blocking on the web request. It's a worker job.\n- Do NOT ingest Gmail history outside the project alias (cross-project bleed is prohibited).\n- Do NOT remove the `approved_for_ai=false` default for bootstrap candidates.\n- Do NOT modify Brief 1 or Brief 2 contracts in breaking ways.\n\n## Workflow expectations\n\n1. Create branch `feat/stage-4-bootstrap-synthesis` off `origin/main` (after Brief 2 merged).\n2. Build in order: migrations → schema → contracts → repositories → fetchers → synthesize → worker task → UI wiring → tests.\n3. **VALIDATE BEFORE DONE**: run `pnpm typecheck && pnpm lint && pnpm test:unit`. Do not declare done until all three pass (or the macOS rollup gotcha is the only failure — note it explicitly).\n4. PR title: `feat(ai): baseline knowledge bootstrap via LLM synthesis (Stage 4 Brief 3/3)`\n5. Surface product-shape ambiguities as PR-description notes rather than inventing behavior.\n\n## Recommended model + effort\n\n**GPT-5.4 — Extra High.** Multi-pass LLM synthesis with structured output, HTML extraction edge cases, masked digesting, admin UI + run status, multiple failure modes. Exactly the shape where Extra High earns its cost.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
